---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../components/PageHeader.astro';
import CtaSection from '../../components/CtaSection.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const lang = 'en';
const pathname = Astro.url.pathname;
---

<Layout title="About - Arcanesys" lang={lang} description="Why we built this, why now, what this is not. Independent, EU-based, sovereignty-first by design. Manuel Wegria / Vincent Romagnoli.">
  <PageHeader
    lang={lang}
    pathname={pathname}
    titleKey="pageHeader.about.title"
    subtitleKey="pageHeader.about.subtitle"
  />

  <article class="prose max-w-prose mx-auto px-10 py-12">

    <h2><span class="num">01</span>Why we built this</h2>
    <p>
      We managed NixOS fleets for years before we built NixFleet. The four crises listed on
      the home page are not academic. They were the daily texture of operations: configuration
      drift on infrastructure we could not prove was identical, sovereignty exposure on cloud
      control planes we did not control, security bolted on by detection tools we could not
      reason about, and compliance produced as PDFs by humans rather than as signed evidence
      by the system.
    </p>
    <p>
      NixFleet is the framework we wanted: the signed-artifact chain end-to-end, magic
      rollback as a protocol property, compliance as a release gate. The point is not novelty.
      The point is that each of these properties already exists in the Nix model. We
      assembled them.
    </p>

    <h2><span class="num">02</span>Why now</h2>
    <p>
      NIS2 transposition deadlines have passed. DORA is applicable to financial entities
      since January 2025. ANSSI BP-028 v2.0 is the reference for French infrastructure
      hardening. Operators under these regimes need declarative tooling that produces signed
      evidence as a side effect of normal operation, not a separate compliance project
      layered on top of an imperative stack.
    </p>

    <h2><span class="num">03</span>What this is not</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Not a startup story.</strong> No funding round, no valuation, no IPO trajectory. The open core funds itself through Pro and Enterprise tiers. The surplus funds open-source work.</li>
      <li><strong>Not AI-anything.</strong> NixFleet is a systems framework. The trust model relies on cryptographic primitives, not on probabilistic inference.</li>
      <li><strong>Not VC-backed.</strong> Independent, EU-based, sovereignty-first by design and by economics.</li>
      <li><strong>Not pretending to be 50 people.</strong> Founder plus ecosystem. The framework benefits from the broader NixOS community. Commercial work is delivered by a small core.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2><span class="num">04</span>Founders</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Vincent Romagnoli</strong> — pilots, partnerships, public-facing outreach.</li>
      <li><strong>Manuel Wegria</strong> — architecture, release engineering.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Pilot enquiries: <a href="mailto:contact@arcanesys.fr">contact@arcanesys.fr</a>.
      Security reports: <a href="mailto:security@arcanesys.fr">security@arcanesys.fr</a>.
    </p>

    <h2><span class="num">05</span>Where to find the code</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/arcanesys/nixfleet">arcanesys/nixfleet</a>: framework, agent, control plane, CLI, CI</li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/arcanesys/nixfleet-compliance">arcanesys/nixfleet-compliance</a>: 16 controls + governance engine</li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/arcanesys/nixfleet-demo">arcanesys/nixfleet-demo</a>: 4-VM reference fleet</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="text-center mt-10">
      <a href={`/${lang}/contact/`} class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[1.5px] uppercase text-indigo hover:text-indigo-hover no-underline">
        Open a conversation →
      </a>
    </p>
  </article>

  <CtaSection lang={lang} />
  <Footer lang={lang} />
</Layout>
